/*
╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║              ZAI Chatbot Configuration (.z-ai-config)                    ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1. Copy this file to .z-ai-config (remove the .example extension):
   cp .z-ai-config.example .z-ai-config

2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual API credentials

3. Restart your development server for the changes to take effect

4. Verify configuration by visiting: http://localhost:3000/api/chatbot/config


REQUIRED FIELDS:
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  baseUrl (string)
    Your AI API endpoint URL
    Examples:
      • OpenAI: "https://api.openai.com/v1"
      • Custom: "https://api.your-service.com/v1"

  apiKey (string)
    Your API authentication key
    Example: "sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
    Note: This should be kept secret and never committed to version control


OPTIONAL FIELDS:
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  chatId (string)
    Optional identifier for chat sessions
    Useful for tracking conversations in the AI system

  userId (string)
    Optional identifier for user tracking
    Helps with personalization and analytics


SECURITY NOTES:
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

⚠️  IMPORTANT: Add .z-ai-config to your .gitignore file to prevent
    accidental exposure of your API credentials!

⚠️  Never share your .z-ai-config file or commit it to version control

⚠️  Use environment variables in production for enhanced security
    (see .env.example for reference)


TROUBLESHOOTING:
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

If the chatbot remains in fallback mode after setting up the config:

1. Check server logs for validation errors
2. Verify JSON syntax is valid (use a JSON validator)
3. Ensure baseUrl is a complete, valid URL
4. Confirm apiKey is not a placeholder value
5. Check file permissions on .z-ai-config (should be readable)
6. Try the configuration check endpoint: /api/chatbot/config


FOR MORE HELP:
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

• Configuration status: /api/chatbot/config
• Example file: .z-ai-config.example
• Documentation: See z-ai-web-dev-sdk documentation

